The paper proposes a technique to detect and generate patterns in a network of locally interacting dynamical systems. This involves the use of a novel spatial superposition logic, which is learned from positive and negative examples of several types of patterns. The paper also integrates model checking algorithm with particle swarm optimization in a computational framework for synthesis of parameters leading to desired patterns in reaction-diffusion systems. Based on these aspects, the most likely sub-category is cs.MS (Mathematical Software). Other likely sub-categories include cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
